f|_U
f: \mathbb{R}^3 \to \mathbb{R}^3, f(r,\theta,z)=(r\cos\theta,r\sin\theta,z).
g
g:U\to f(U), g(r,\theta,z)=f(r,\theta,z).
g
f(U) = \mathbb{R}^3 \setminus \{(x,y,z) : y = 0, x > 0\}
y\neq 0
g^{-1}
g
g^{-1} = \begin{cases}\left(\sqrt{x^2+y^2}, \arccos \frac{y}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}, z\right) & y \geq 0\\ \left(\sqrt{x^2+y^2}, 2\pi - \arccos \frac{y}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}, z\right) & y < 0, \end{cases}
\lim_{\textbf{q}\to(x,0,z)} g^{-1}(\textbf{q}) = (-x,\pi,z),
